About us
The brick and rich, dark wood interior takes you a thousand miles from Florida as soon as you enter. A veritable museum of Red Sox memorabilia adorns the walls. An endless variety of microbrews and comfort beers hold their own against a wine list forty bottles strong. Gourmet sandwiches rule the menu. Hearty soups and bountiful, crisp salads are perfect teammates to the Panini and baked brie. We only use fresh ingredients of the highest quality to craft our food.
Here at Lansdowne Street you can indulge in authentic New England cuisine in a setting that looks and feels like a Boston pub without ever leaving Bonita Springs. Lansdowne Street is the only restaurant and bar in Bonita Springs specializing in New England Sports. We've got plenty of televisions and show all the Red Sox, Patriots and Celtics games as they happen. Watch the games the way they do in Boston...with a Fenway-style crowd of like-minded fans cheering on the team.
End Section 2

Groups and parties
we host your party
Kick back and relax to live music with a cold beer and great food. The cozy lounge and indoor/outdoor atmosphere provide the perfect creative meeting space or socializing spot. With a buzzing brunch scene, live music, and late-night DJs, Shea's. is an ideal spot for all occasions - birthdays, bachelorette parties, date nights, and more.
